content: Didn't get past the confirm language screen. Everything froze.

Occasionally glitches, refuses to allow people to gain reputation. The moment that inspired this review though was when a high scoring 10th game occurred and the 2nd place player only was able to place 4 of her 21 glory. This killed our motivation to finish the last 2 scenarios.
Frozen
Good implementation, but it will not add to my family library. The active switch keeps resetting to grey/off.

Great game. Having fun with 5 other friends. There needs to be options if a player lapses their time limit though. Having them just be replaced by an ai is rough as they can not be reinvited to the game without us having to restart the game.. Maybe a voting system of kick or wait, or just retrieve all and skip their turn? It would also be great to have more clear notification settings (or even have them enabled by default) so other players know when it's their turn,and even additional reminders.

Love the game but had to buy this version because the Nintendo Switch version keeps crashing on multiplayer. A shame too, because I was excited to play on Nintendo Switch, but buying multiple copies just be continue a game, sucks. Btw, it not just me, my wife and another friend bought the Switch version, and multiplayer crashes on all of them. We had to all buy android/ios versions just to be able to keep playing. :(
Issues are being fixed. Good adaptation of the physical game.

Very few issues in the single player campaign. I did find one bug that I've sent forward. We had some issues with matchmaking online last night but gonna try again tonight. If we can get it rolling I'll update it to 5 stars. Love the game, super fun, just a few kinks that need to be worked out!

Update to my previous issue. I ended up deleting the app and downloaded it again. While installing and the initial loading of the game I made sure my screen stayed on. Now the game plays great and I get to enjoy some worker placement. Not sure if my device was losing its connection and corrupted my install or what. Hope this helps if anyone else has issues. Game loads to menu but that's where it stops. Hopefully they fix whatever bug this is or else I just wasted money
replyContent:
Hello, 
Could you please send us more information about your issue? You can contact us at contact@acram.eu. We'll be happy to look at this for you.
Thanks!

content: Finished game 5 and hit next game. When the next game came up it was game 5 again. We played through the second time and finally made it to game 6. During the first turn of game 6 some kind of bug happened when the red player placed his worker on a red blight token using the persona that lets you immediately retrieve the worker. It went into an infinite loop and his turn would never end. Couldn't proceed past this no matter what I tried. Edit: Now with update we are up and running again!

Bug in game. Running a solo campaign and it has made me take the same last five turns of level five several times. Then today, it let's me start to take those SAME turns again, but this time, it just freezes. The recent update must have caused issues!
replyContent: We have fixed this issue a few patches back. Please give it a try!

content: DONT BUY, TERRIBLE BUG. I've played through the campagin seven times now, until I get to the end of game 3. The game wont move onto game four no matter what you click or how long you give it to finish. Whats worse it loads game 3 up again and takes anything you had in your capacity from game two. So you get to not only play the same game over and over you get robbed before you start. This is trash, complete trash. I'll be getting a refund.
replyContent: We'd love to understand what went wrong with your game. Please email us at contact@acram.eu so that we can try to fix it for you.

content: Really fun, complex
Great implementation of an awesome board game

Straight copy/paste of the rules from the board game with no thought of how it works with asynchronous play. Having to open the app to retrieve your workers when you have nothing else to do feel terrible. Income can wait to be taken until the start of a player's turn. Artwork is great, game implementation not so much

Amazing board game port! Possibly the best on Android! Bugs are constantly being exterminated. All of this developer's games are incredibly fun, especially Eight-Minute Empire. All of their games are incredibly easy recommendations for me!

So laggy it hurts. Beautiful, great implementation of one of my favorite boardgames, but even on a powerful, updated, device it's horribly laggy, still laggy even with the options set for better performance. For 10 bucks pretty disappointed, nearly unplayable and totally not fun by game 4 because the game lags so hard. Really hoping they can optimize soon, otherwise I just flushed 10 bucks. Sadface.

There's a bug with the glory and the last category where the benefit isn't being used. I earned that benefit at the end of game 3 and in game 4 it doesn't work. Completely negated the glory rewards of the first 3 games which is very frustrating. Started over and replayed 3 games and confirmed that it will not let me pick 2 of that object at the beginning of game 4.
I got a brand new tablet ( Lenovo Android 9.0, 3 gigs of RAM, Cortex 1.80 GHz CPU) and this game late SOOOO bad that it's basically unplayable. Not what I expected of a $10 app.
Disappointed at the number of basic functionality bugs for a paid / released app. Now I can't sign in again. Very close to demanding a refund, as this app has been a headache so many times.

App is not working. It was working fine up until 2 days ago, in which it stopped working well. Then I uninstalled and installed again and it literally doesn't do anything now other than a menu GUI. I'm about to time out in a game and I wanted to trust the work you guys were doing, but this has to be the worst app experience I've ever had. And it's the first time I've heard of a software working worse after a wipe.

Not ready for prime time. Continually have to exit to the lobby to advance the game. Now getting a server error -2 message in game 6. Going to be really disappointed if it needs to be deleted. Can't imagine my group starting again if forced to.
Cool game but very buggy and you'll spend 90% of the time in loading screens for asynchronous games

The physical game was one of my favorite gaming experiences. Unfortunately the digital version released unfinished. Initially seen in some rough edges and frequent patches more akin to a beta, the campaign I had started with friends finally came to a crashing halt when several members were no longer able to load the campaign on their Android devices, and were then auto-kicked by the default time limit for moves. Thus, even after the game is patched, we would have to restart our whole campaign.

Pretty good implemention and looks pretty. But... Very laggy as you make you moves. Drag and drop basically does not function. Most importantly they put out updates for steam and iOS but not Android and I am going to miss my turn because others updated and I could not. With cross play they should never have released like this if it caused an error. I was suggest waiting to buy and play this till it is actually ready for release. Edit from 2 to 1 star as I just got kick out of my game.

Can not play. Several turns into a game with 5 friends and no matter what device I log into: "Operation Failed - Message from server: Invalid saved game data. Error Code: -2" Completely reinstalled on 2 different devices. And if you get that fixed, please enable an option to auto pick up my guys if that is literally the only thing I have to do on my turn. Thanks.
The bosrdgame is excellent, this app is trash. Often get stuck in infinite load - turn - crash - load loops. Theyre charging full price for an app that isn't finished !

A truly fantastic job condensing a rather complex game into a very useable format. There are bugs here and there, but the developers are quickly dealing with them. Biggest issue is the lack of tutorial. My advice is to read the in-game rulebook completely and take it slow. By the end of the first game, it all made sense to me, but it was an awkward first impression. Also, the performance is not great. Admittedly I am using an older device, but I still feel like there's room for optimization
Interesting game, good app, I appreciate the modest size (<120MB) for such a complicated game.

The gameplay itself is pretty well done. But the lack of a tutorial is inexcusable and I'm constantly getting push notifications that it's my turn when it isn't. There also needs to be a way to go from one game to another without having to go back to the lobby. Rating will go up if they make some improvements.

Currently. At version 1.0.3, this feels like an early beta version. During online play of a campaign, we have had to close and reopen the app multiple times to get the game to synch up correctly. After finishing game 7/12, our save data became invalid and we can't continue. I miss being able to name each character and the other charters. I'm playing through the campaign with the same person I played through the physical version with and that name recognition removes a lot of the heart for me
replyContent: Could you please check the latest 1.0.4 version? The bugs with saving campaigns should be fixed. Also, the 1.0.5 version with more fixes is currently under beta tests and will be published soon.

content: Beautiful look, developers have been working hard to make the online experience as enjoyable as the board game!
Love the game, and it is great to see the game constantly being updated. 5 stars!

Great game. Writing review to let developers know that there seems to be a bug where the capacity rule doesn't actually start to apply at all. It greys the rule out of the rulebook and then doesn't ever start applying after the second game as it should. Which means everyone carried everything over to the next game.

I've played about 5 games so far and I love it. I haven't played the physical board game, but was very interested in it, so was excited to download the digital edition. There's a couple pieces of the rules that aren't explained super well, but the tutorial is good enough to give me a basic grip of the game.
The start screen is pretty. But it wont let me advance passed it. Local play just shows up blank and online wont let me register.

Okay going middle of road. I am sure game is actually amazing. I feel tutorial could be better. I feel like I am just moving my guys around, can't build anything new. Went and read how to build but unsure if I have to meet some sorta of goal before. Update: So seeing cost on cards help. So I can say I am enjoying. I still want physical copy one of theses days.
